text:
At the weekend in Kiev will change the routes of some buses and trolleybuses

01 Nov 2019, 20:15


In connection with the holding of fairs in Kiev on the weekend, the routes of some buses and trolleybuses will be changed.

This was reported by the press service of Kyivpastrans KP.
"On November 2, the routes of buses No. 6, 49, 61, 87, 95 and trolleybuses No. 34, 37A, and November 3 - buses No. 31 will be changed," the statement said.
According to information, food fairs are planned in the streets of Liskovsky, Marina Tsvetaeva, Jordan, Ambrosiy Buchma and Tatarskaya.
As noted, from the beginning of the movement to the end (approximately until 18:00) the movement will be organized:

trolley bus number 34 from the street. North, then - Ave. Heroes of Stalingrad - st. Marshal Tymoshenko - Ave. Heroes of Stalingrad - st. Stepan Bandera;
trolley bus number 37A - from st. m. "Forest" to the street Liskovsky on the existing highway, then along the route of route No. 37;
bus number 6 from Darnitskaya Square to the street. Miloslavskaya (without arrival on Liskovsky St. and Radunskaya St.);
bus number 61 from the hall. pl. "Troyeshchina" to the street Radunskaya (without arrival on Liskovsky St.);
bus number 49 from the hall. pl. "Left Bank" to the street Ambrosia Buchma on the existing highway, then Ave. Pavel Tychina - Dnieper embankment, then along the existing highway;



Zik


bus number 87 in the direction of st. Metropolitan Andrey Sheptytsky, from Art. m. "Osokorki" to the street Ambrosia Buchma on the existing highway, then Ave. Pavel Tychyna - st. Bereznyakovskaya, then along the existing highway;



Zik


bus number 95 in the direction of the Nikolskaya Slobodka massif, from the hall. pl. "Left Bank" to the street Ambrosia Buchma on the existing highway, then Ave. Pavel Tychina - Dnieper embankment, then along the existing highway;



Zik


bus number 31 from the metro station "Polytechnic Institute" to the street. Otto Schmidt on the current highway, then - st. Otto Schmidt - ul. Nagornaya, then along the existing highway.

Recall that from November 1 in Kiev on seven streets they limited the speed on the roads.

